
[1]earnestly

   EARNESTLY, adv. ern'estly. Warmly; zealously; importunately; eagerly;
   with real desire.

   Being in an agony, he prayed more earnestly. Luke 22.

   That ye should earnestly contend for the faith once delivered to the
   saints. Jude 3.

   2. With fixed attention; with eagerness.

   A certain maid looked earnestly upon him. Luke 22.
